column29: So hard time with olivine stability, and in general hard to get it to crystallize, BUT had some luck once moving more reducing than NNO -2

SO since I was unable to get Olivine at NNO for MG and also for most MI (all but 13b) and could only get it at NNO -2, I ran some uncorrected MI comps at NNO to see if we get olivine! To see if that’s the source of the issue
Only olivine at really shallow pressures (75 and 50)
Only olivine at really shallow pressures (75 and 50)
olivine only crystallizes at 325 which is when plag and cpx have a cotectic! Interesting
Fo and An are at expected pressure!
don’t have what we want now but we are working towards this
plot expected pressure with the three possible cotectics
Note I have more runs of MG from cerro negro than reported here, but all failed to crystallize olivine at any number of redox states
Aka had to be NNO-2 or below!

Note this issue was seen in both MG and MI, but could test the stability in MI's since they were both corrected and not corrected, AND they are olivine hosted so they should be crystallizing olivine!!!!! So good test reguardless of the pressure estimating method, its a good test to see what is causing olivine to not be stable: MELTS or the PEC corrections (the comps themselves)
